----<br>
Hehe, not only do I play on Guinevere, but during early Euro hours, and apparently it is already much worse for mids at this time (but actually, the &quot;winning&quot; side during this timezone is Albion).<br>
<br>
That been said :<br>
Bigger picture.<br>
Left Axe was overpowered, period. End regen, I hesitate to say overpowered ... but very powerful indeed. The block and parry rates ... it was a bug, and a bug has to be fixed. Thanks for our warriors.<br>
Things needed to be done. There should have been adjustments.<br>
But my big complaints, is that they are overnerfing. They could have just changed end regen to a chant, voila, problem solved. But no, they had to design a system from scratch, unheard of since the beginning of the cam, to give them both the disadvantages of chants and conc buffs. It is not a nerf bat, it is a nerf sledgehammer.<br>
For left axe ... the doubled style bonuses (compared with what CD/DW had) were a bit over the top. However, the reduction should have been something like 20%, not 50%. Now, LA damage is equal with CD DW.<br>
Does this make the class balanced ? No. Because Mythic has always stated that balance was not purely a class by class affair, but a realm wide issue.<br>
I am sorry, but Hibernia have advantages in the spellcasting department (compare enchanters with spiritmasters). Albion has a truckload of &quot;defensive melee&quot; abilities unique to the realm (ablative song, AF chant that goes overcap, plate armor, plus the unbalanced RA's like BoF or SoS we have all learned to love ...). High melee damage (both with zerker firepower, and more styling because of endurance) was &quot;the&quot; unique thing in Midgard.<br>
Who next will do the damage dealing in Midgard (don't say savages, they will be hit by the nerf bat sooner or later imho). Warriors ? They got love in the form of defense boosting, but they are just that, defensive. Thanes ? Skalds ? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Hunters ? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   There is not just enough cloth casters in Midgard (not that they are weak, though I really think spiritmasters could receive a bit of love, but because an abundance of them doesn't fit the theme of the realm , and there are no real compelling reason for players who want to roll casters to go to the melee realm). That's a thing that must be considered.<br>
<br>
What was done in this patch is a perfect equalization between the light tank classes. No one better. They are absolutely making sure that there is no compelling reason at all to choose a berzerker above a blademaster or a mercenary.<br>
<br>
On first looks, it's great.<br>
<br>
On second thought, if all other aspects of the game and of realm balance are not equalized exactly the same way.<br>
<br>
In other words :<br>
- Yes, some adjustments had to be done.<br>
- However if THOSE changes go live, it will be a disaster if there is no Midgard (in general, and for the nerfed classed in particular) love going with this patch.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just additional food for thought :<br>
What is the point of playing a warrior (heavy tank in midgard) compared to a post patch mercenary (albion light tank) ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 290<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/25/03 9:00:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=588.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oh</span><hr size=1> Oh, and whatever happens, that patch alone will not make me cancel or reroll. <br>
